Disaster for our #22 car at Round 2 at NJ Motorsports Park, as a sudden failure in Cylinder 3 of our Prelude's H22 engine caused it to start spewing oil out of the vents on our Prelude's catch can. Apologies to the competitors behind us who came across the oil that landed on track.

It's a disappointing way to end a weekend that started with so much promise: Our Saturday qualifying times were a full second faster than at our last visit in October despite the sweltering heat.

Race report and in-car video coming soon.

