I'm sick. I didn't sleep well. I didn't get all of my meals in. I don't have time. Listen, if your training routine is a constant barrage of excuses, you need to put that weight down because that half-assed movement isn’t going to get you anywhere except nowhere. The best athletes take care of business under ALL conditions, not just ideal ones. Excuses are like a cancer. Once it infects your brain, it spreads everywhere, including your heart. And when excuses take over your heart, you might as well retire—the heart is the only thing that’s going to keep you going when the energy gets low and the body starts to falter. Your choice. #NoExcuses #TakeCareOfBusiness 📸 credits: @brianmossphoto 
