I will be on stage again in exactly 5 weeks from now. As always loaded on ice cream apple pies and cookies. Dry to the point where my feet hurt and looking like death. 
BUT something will be different. Something I failed to remember during the last shows I had competed in:
I LOVE BODYBUILDING with all my heart and I cherish every moment of being able to live my dream.
I will never pressure myself to look a certain way that I don't like. I will never worry about what people might say and most important I will never again let anything get my mind to the point where my passion turns into a torturous monotony of frustration.
I owe this to the 15 year old boy who picked up his first rusty weight 14 years ago in the tiny weight room of his boarding home and ever since then put his whole life into on day being an IFBB Pro. 
It has brought so much fun and joy into my sad and lonely life back then and right now i feel the exact same way again. 
Thank God I was remembered.
#AllesAusNichts .
